description:
On September 30, 2018 I had the pleasure of interviewing, bassist, composer, and improvisor Miroslav Vitouš, at the Artist Talk series of the Frauenfeld International Festival "Generations". We had time to delve into some of the groundbreaking work he played an important part of the late 1960's and beyond, such as the "Now He Sings, Now He Sobs" session, the formation of Weather report, as well as his evolution as a band leader which among other things put the bass in the foreground. We also explored his focus on the importance of conversation, open communication and new roles between players inspired by his unique way of structuring and improvising music.

Please note that due to copyright restrictions on some of the music material played in the interview the video goes mute during those sections. I fought these copyright restrictions and in some cases was successful in restoring the audio, but there are three music sections  I could not attain permission.

The video is taken from a Facebook livestream video from the festival. 

http://www.generations.ch
